        <div n="327-47L4" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-1"> As T<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">HOMAS</hi> was Cudgel'd one Day by his Wife,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-2"> He took to the Street and fled for his Life;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-3"> T<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">OM'S</hi> three dearest Friends came by in the Squabble,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-4"> And sav'd him at once from the Shrew and the Rabble, And sav'd him at once from the Shrew and the Rabble.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="5" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-5">Then ventur'd to give him some sober Advice,&#13;</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-6"> But T<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">OM</hi> is a Person of Honour so nice,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-7"> Too wise to take Council, too proud to take warning,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-8"> That he sent to all three a Challenge next morning, that he sent to all three a Challenge next morning.</l></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l n="9" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-9">Three Duels he fought, Thrice ventur'd his Life his Life-------- ventur'd his Life,&#13;</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-327-47L4-line-10"> went home----- went home----- and was Cudgel'd a-----gain by his Wife, was Cudgel'd a-----gain by his Wife.327-47L4   </l></lg></div>
